title: Super Putty.png
comments.comment:
Is it trusted?

I mean, do we know it's not a honey-pot?; +Michael Poloni In order to get jobs done quickly, it doesn't matter whether it's honey or poison I will take it ...; +Terrence Miao remind me never to let you loose on one of our production machines ... ; I dropped Putty a while back simply because there's no easy way to do a real clear screen (reset terminal and clear buffer, in Putty terms) in a single keyboard shortcut.

Cygwin bash and ssh a-we-go.

And, if you want to quickly switch between multiple windows, if you're in Win7 (which, +Terrence Miao, you seem to be), is made SO easy with a keyboard shortcut that works like OS X's CMD-~.
